notes: |
  Boil down some decent red wine until Ribena consistency.
steps:
  - season flour and coat short ribs
  - step: 'per 100g short rib: flour, salt, pepper'
    substeps:
      - 5g flour
      - 0.3g salt
      - 0.1g pepper (50:50 black:white)
  - brown at 170°C in a dutch oven
  - keep moving to not burn fond
  - chop leek, celery, carrot, and shallots
  - remove short ribs
  - set to 130°C, add shallots, add lid, sweat down and caramelise for 5 mins or so
  - add remaining veg & 2 crushed cloves of garlic, keep moving for fond
  - add 2 tbsp of tomato puree and cook down
  - meat back in
  - heat off
  - boiled down red wine in
  - beef stock in
  - add herbs (parsley, bay) for aromat
  - add cartouche
  - 140°C oven for 4 hours -> 80°C for 10 hours
  - leave to cool in sauce for 40 mins ish
  - remove meat carefully
  - strain remaining sauce
  - boil down until desired consistency
  - make slurry with wholegrain mustard and sherry vinegar with a bit of sauce, then integrate until desired flavour (+ general seasoning)
